<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Bangladesh </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Receives Pakistani Naval Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Receives Pakistani Naval Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1905031594 Dhaka Radio Bangladesh Network in English 0130 
GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1905031594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dhaka Radio Bangladesh Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The visiting three-member Pakistan naval delegation 
led by its navy chief, Admiral Sayeed M. Khan, met President 
Abdur Rahman Biswas at Bangabhaban [President House] in Dhaka 
yesterday. While exchanging views with Adm. Sayeed, President 
Biswas appreciated the cooperation between the navies of the two 
countries. The Pakistan Navy chief assured to continue their 
help to Bangladesh Navy for its development. He appreciated the 
progress of the Bangladesh Navy. Bangladesh Navy chief Rear 
Admiral Mohammad Mohaimenul Islam was present. 

</TEXT>

