<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Bangladesh </F>
<H3> <TI>   Australia To Give $1.6 Million in Technical Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Australia To Give $1.6 Million in Technical Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2005105194 Dhaka Radio Bangladesh Network in Bengali 1230 
GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2005105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Dhaka Radio Bangladesh Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bengali </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Australia will provide technical assistance of 40 
crore 58 lakh taka, equivalent to $1.6 million, for the wheat 
development project of the Wheat Research Center of the 
Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute. A memorandum of 
understanding to this effect was signed in Dhaka today. The 
Australian high commissioner in Bangladesh, (Kenneth W. 
Askiner), and the joint secretary of the Economic Relations 
Division of the Ministry of Finance, A.S.M. Alamgir, signed the 
memorandum on behalf of their respective governments. This 
technical assistance will be utilized for research and training 
and for increasing the institutional authority of the Wheat 
Research Center. 

</TEXT>

