<H3> <TI>   Khamene'i Pardons Prisoners To Mark 'Id al-Adha </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khamene'i Pardons Prisoners To Mark 'Id al-Adha </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005095794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] On the occasion of the auspicious anniversary of 
the 'Id al-Adha and 'Id al-Ghadir, His Eminence Ayatollah 
Khamene'i, the eminent leader of the Islamic revolution and the 
guardian of the cause of Muslims, pardoned or reduced the 
sentences of 2,289 persons convicted by Islamic revolution, 
general, and military courts throughout the country. 
