<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   ETTELA'AT Launches International Edition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ETTELA'AT Launches International Edition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905171094 Tehran IRNA in English 1659 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] London, May 19, IRNA -- The London office of the 
Persian daily ETTELA'AT announced Thursday that it had 
successfully issued its special international edition in New 
York for the first time this week. 
  The international edition was launched initially in London 
two months ago as a weekly to cater for the Iranian community in 
the UK and elsewhere in Europe. Its 12-page format includes a 
section in English and was said to have proved very popular. 
  The paper is edited in Tehran and beamed for publication by 
satellite to London as well as New York, which will assist the 
speed of publication throughout America. 
  Plans were said by ETTELA'AT to be well advanced for a 
special daily international edition, which could start as early 
as next week and like the weekly version, will differ in content 
to the Persian afternoon edition available in Tehran. 
  The London office spoke favorably about the successful 
launch 
of Iran's first newspaper to be printed abroad since the Islamic 
revolution, which is available from newsagents, Iranian shops or 
through subscription. 

</TEXT>

