Daily Report 
<DATE1>  17 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Asad Receives FAO Director General </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Asad Receives FAO Director General </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1705172294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1705172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Hafiz al-Asad received Jack Dyuf, the 
director general of the UN's Food and Agriculture Organization 
[FAO] at 1215 today. The meeting was attended by Agriculture 
Minister As'ad Mustafa and the FAO Damascus office director, 
Mustafa Nasir. Talks dealt with the organization's role in 
agricultural development in the world and in realizing food 
security in the future. 
  The president expressed Syria's appreciation for the FAO 
efforts and Syria's eagerness to cooperate with it to realize 
its aims. 
  The FAO director expressed admiration for the Syrian 
agricultural policy and promised that the FAO will contribute 
toward raising Syria's agricultural production capacity. 
  The FAO director left Damascus today after a two-day visit 
during which he met with President Hafiz al-Asad. 
  He was seen off by As'ad Mustafa, the Agriculture Minister, 
Yahya Baqqur, director general of the Arab Organization for 
Agricultural Development; the assistant agriculture minister; 
the regional FAO representative in Damascus; and senior 
agriculture Ministry and UN officials in Damascus. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

