<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kurdish Islamic Movement Reports Clashes With PUK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kurdish Islamic Movement Reports Clashes With PUK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905190494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905190494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for the Islamic Movement in Iraqi 
Kurdistan has announced that his movement carried out military 
operations yesterday, during which it regained Tappah Kurrah, 
(Muhammad Abad), (Kumalar), Anab, Bakrawah, Sirah, and Halabjah 
from the forces of the Patriot Union of Kurdistan [PUK], at the 
same time killing a number of PUK troops. 
  The spokesman added that the Islamic Movement is continuing 
its advance and is besieging the city of Sayyid Sadiq. 
  He added that during their occupation of the above-mentioned 
villages, Jalal Talabani's forces violated people's honor, 
carried out murders and massacres, and stole livestock. 
  The Islamic Movement spokesman said that the citizens of 
Shanaderi Khwaru fled to the plains and wadis to escape the PUK 
forces' assaults. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

