<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Urges Mutually Acceptable Hajj Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Urges Mutually Acceptable Hajj Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005104294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The unifying Friday prayers were held throughout 
the country simultaneously today. In Tehran, the prayers were 
led by Hojjat ol-Eslam val Moslemin Hashemi-Rafsanjani. [passage 
omitted] 
  In his second sermon, the president of the Islamic Republic 
of Iran pointed to the restrictions placed by the Saudi 
government on the holding of the disavowal of infidels ceremony. 
He said: The Saudis could have acted more sensibly and not 
caused differences between the two important countries of the 
region. Today, Islamic unity is a principle as important for us 
as the disavowal of infidels principle. He added: Considering 
the crisis points in various parts of the world, and with the 
wise leadership of the honorable leader of the Islamic 
revolution [Khamene'i], another crisis was averted over this 
matter. 
  The president advised the Saudis to think harder and to take 
on more correct methods in future years. He said: We hope that 
in the future, a program on the hajj acceptable to both 
countries will be formulated which will take into account the 
views of both sides. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

