<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Asad, King Husayn Begin Damascus Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Asad, King Husayn Begin Damascus Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2005112394 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1100 GMT 
20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2005112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] With God's care and protection, His Majesty King 
Husayn today arrived in Damascus on a brief visit to the Syrian 
Arab Republic. Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad led those who 
received his majesty at Damascus International Airport. Also 
receiving the king were Vice Presidents 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam 
and Zuhayr Mashariqah, Prime Minister Mahmud al-Zu'bi, the 
deputy prime ministers, Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar, 
ministers, and several senior Syrian officials, as well as Ahmad 
al-'Adayilah, Jordan's ambassador in Damascus, and his embassy 
staff. 
  Arriving with the king were Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, the 
prime minister; al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir, chief of the Royal 
Hashemite Court; and Marwan al-Qasim, his majesty the king's 
political adviser. 
  After shaking hands with those who were on hand to receive 
him, the king, accompanied by President Hafiz al-Asad, left for 
the People's Palace, where talks between the two parties 
started. The talks are cochaired by His Majesty King Husayn and 
President Hafiz al-Asad. 

</TEXT>

