<H3> <TI>   Police Force Reportedly `Not in Control' in Gaza </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Force Reportedly `Not in Control' in Gaza </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2005093494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 20 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2005093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Palestinian police force is not in control of 
the situation in the Gaza Strip and has even ceased trying to 
handle traffic. Our correspondent Nisim Qeynan has learned from 
Arab sources that armed and unmasked Hamas [Islamic Resistance 
Movement] members have been roaming around the Gaza Strip 
undisturbed since yesterday. 
  Nabil Sha'th, head of the PLO delegation, arrived in the 
strip from Egypt last night for a 24-hour visit. He is holding 
talks with Palestinian police commanders and others on the 
functioning of the police force in the autonomy, as well as on 
different matters. 

</TEXT>

