<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Patrols Begin in Khan Yunus, Gaza City </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Patrols Begin in Khan Yunus, Gaza City </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2105112594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 21 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2105112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Joint Palestinian-Israeli patrols began operating 
today in the areas of Khan Yunus and Gaza city. According to 
the agreement, the patrols will travel on three routes along the 
Netzarim, Morag, and Qatif Bloc roads. 
  Each patrol will include two jeeps. A Palestinian officer 
and three policemen will ride in one vehicle, whereas the other 
jeep will carry an Israeli Border Police officer and three 
soldiers. 
  Our Army affairs correspondent Karmela Menashe reports that 
the length of each route five to seven kilometers and the units 
patrolling it will be responsible for maintaining security in 
the area. There will also be a joint Palestinian-Israeli foot 
patrol in the vicinity of the Erez checkpoint and at the 
entrance to the Gaza Strip. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

