<H3> <TI>   Fatah Hawks `Terrorists' Join Security Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Hawks `Terrorists' Join Security Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2205142094 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew 22 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> TA2205142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITIM] </F>
  [Text] Seventy Fatah Hawks terrorists were recruited to 
the Palestinian security forces in the Gaza Strip yesterday. 
  Of the 70 -- who constitute the total number of Fatah's 
terrorists and fugitives -- some 30 will be incorporated into 
the Palestinian police force; approximately 20 will join the 
security service under Muhammad Dahlan's command, while the rest 
will join the military force, or will renounce this privilege 
and become civilians. 
  A senior Israeli source said the Israeli security forces 
were 
unaware of this agreement. 

</TEXT>

