<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Palestinian Association for Human Rights today 
appealed to the amir of the State of Kuwait for an immediate 
pardon to 10 Palestinian students who were sentenced to death by 
the Kuwait State Security Court on 12 June last year. 
  The association requests the amir of Kuwait to respond to 
the 
appeal of the families and kinfolk of those sentenced to pardon 
their sons during these holy months and on the occasion of the 
blessed 'Id al-Adha. 
  It is worth mentioning that the appeal court will issue its 
ruling about the sentences against the students on 30 May in 
response to the appeal submitted by the convicted students. 

