Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fugitive `Terrorists' Caught in Security Sweep </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fugitive `Terrorists' Caught in Security Sweep </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2005170394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1530 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2005170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, 20 May (MENA) -- Today, in a security sweep 
in Asyut, Upper Egypt, security forces caught 17 fugitive 
terrorists whose cases had been recently tried in various areas 
of Asyut. 
  The sweep included villages and urban centers in Sadafa and 
al-Ghana'im and involved over 1,000 soldiers and officers. A 
total of 25 automatic rifles, 12 semi-automatic rifles, 10 
revolvers, 15 local-made pistols, and 876 rounds were seized. 
  Also, during the sweep, 10 previously convicted for 
felonies, 
five for embezzlement, four in narcotics cases, and 10 minors 
were arrested. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

