<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   JANA Editor Comments on Yemen Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    JANA Editor Comments on Yemen Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2205211894 Tripoli Great Jamahiriyah Radio Network in 
Arabic 1600 GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2205211894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli Great Jamahiriyah Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] In a commentary on the situation in Yemen, JANA's 
Arab Affairs editor said that the collapse of the union in Yemen 
was undoubtedly the work of a reactionary and imperialist 
conspiracy. It is well known that the reactionary and 
imperialist forces, with the blatant hostility they harbor for 
Arab unity, have put a veto on the unity of the Arab nation and 
any unionist achievement between any two or more Arab countries. 
Our contemporary history is full of recent living examples, the 
abortion of the union between Egypt and Syria in 1958, embodied 
in the Arab united republic. Reactionary and imperialist 
schemes were behind the collapse of this union after only three 
years of its foundation. These schemes have also aborted the 
experience of the Arab-African union between Libya and Morocco; 
and there they are today carrying out their scheme against 
Yemen's union and is held responsible for the collapse of this 
four-year old union. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
