<H3> <TI>   Reaction to al-Dirani Seizure Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reaction to al-Dirani Seizure Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Military Source' Announces Raid </H4>

<F P=102> NC2105054694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0520 GMT 21 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2105054694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A military source made the following statement this 
morning: 
  At 0200 today, an Israeli enemy commando force, using two 
helicopters, kidnapped resistance official al-Haj Mustafa 
al-Dirani from his house in Qasr Naba village. The Israeli 
force used the road separating Kasrawan and al-Biqa' to carry 
out its action. 
  It should be recalled that Israeli helicopters were 
monitored 
flying at high altitude last night. The Lebanese army and 
Syrian forces were placed on alert. Patrols pursued the Israeli 
commando force in Qasr Naba and al-Furzul. Ground defenses 
opened fired at the helicopters as they were retreating toward 
the sea. 
  This operation is part of the enemy's piracy and continued 
violations of international laws and norms. 

</TEXT>

