<H4>    Mufti Stresses Resisting Occupation </H4>

<F P=102> NC2105153594 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1300 GMT 21 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2105153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the occasion of the blessed 'Id al-Adha, 
spiritual leaders delivered several sermons today. They 
explained the significance of the 'Id and stressed the need for 
unity and adherence to national principles. 
  Shaykh 'Abd-al-Amir Qabalan, deputy chairman of the Higher 
Shiite Islamic Council and chief Ja'farite mufti, called for 
national unity to confront conspiracies. He stressed the 
importance of resistance as long as the Israeli occupation 
continues. He said: The south and Western al-Biqa' continue to 
be the chief concern, and suffering is growing as a result of 
the Israeli acts of aggression, which burn the land, threaten 
the infrastructure, and displace the people. This is a recording 
of an excerpt from Mufti Qabalan's speech: 
  [Begin recording] What kind of solutions does Israel want? 
It wants us to surrender. It is asking us for the Israeli 
corporal [navigator Ron Arad], so why do we not ask it for 
Shaykh 'Abd-al-Karim 'Ubayd? It is asking us for the corpses of 
the Israeli soldiers, so why do we not ask it for our live 
detainees in its prisons? It is demanding that we stop 
resistance, so why do we not demand that it withdraw from the 
south and Western al-Biqa'? Israel wants everything, and if it 
wants to give something it does so through a dispenser, drop by 
drop. Therefore, we tell the kin and brothers that we have to 
demonstrate solidarity and deal with each other honestly, 
sincerely, amicably, and respectfully. We tell them to avoid 
hatred and tension. Israel does not differentiate between a 
fighter and a non-fighter, between the inhabitants of the border 
strip and the inhabitants of al-Biqa', or between northerners 
and southerners. It views every Arab and Muslim as an enemy 
that must be annihilated. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

