<H3> <TI>   Judge Charges Ja'ja' with Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Judge Charges Ja'ja' with Church Bombing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2005173294 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1700 GMT 20 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2005173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chief Public Prosecutor Judge Munif 'Uwaydat has 
charged Samir Ja'ja', commander of the dissolved Lebanese Forces 
Party, with the bombing of the Sayyidat al-Najat church in Zuq 
Mikha'il. Justice Joseph Furayhah, the judicial investigator of 
this crime, forwarded the file of the interrogation of Ja'ja' to 
the Public Prosecutor's office, and will later hear his 
testimony when Ja'ja is a defendant. 
  Judge Furayhah heard the testimony of retired Major Fu'ad 
Malik, the general commissioner of the dissolved Lebanese Forces 
Party, in his capacity as a witness in other cases. 

</TEXT>

