<H3> <TI>   Army Exercises Mark Khorramshahr's Liberation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Exercises Mark Khorramshahr's Liberation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2205085794 Tehran IRNA in English 0823 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2205085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 22, IRNA -- Thousands of ground forces 
of the Islamic Republic's Army Sunday participated in `Ra'ad 7' 
(thunder) maneuver in Darengon region of Shiraz, Southern Fars 
Province. 
  The public relations office of the Army reported today that 
the five-day maneuver is carried out on the 13th anniversary of 
the liberation of the southern port city of Khorramshahr, 
Khuzestan Province, occupied by the Iraqi forces during the 
Iraqi invasion of Iran in 1981. 
  Electronic equipment as well as heavy and light weapons will 
be used in the military exercise which is being staged to 
further improve the combat power of the forces, the report said. 
  It also added that three more maneuvers are to be launched 
in 
Khuzestan, Khorasan and Tehran Provinces marking the 
Khorramshahr liberation anniversary. 

</TEXT>

