<F P=103> JN2205103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jordan today reiterated its support for Yemeni 
legitimacy and the unity of the Yemeni people, refusing, at the 
same time, to clearly condemn Aden's decision yesterday to 
establish an independent state in the south. 
  Government-run Jordanian radio and television have been 
reporting, without comment, the views of northerners and 
southerners. However, official Jordanian media have recently 
referred to the southerners as the separatist forces, the 
description used by the northerners, who are referred to as the 
government forces. 

