<DOCNO> FBIS4-60182 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes099_j_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-099 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Southern Yemen To Announce Secession From North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Southern Yemen To Announce Secession From North </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Russian Envoy Meets Salih </H4>

<F P=102> JN2305053294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0330 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2305053294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, received at his office 
yesterday evening Igor [word indistinct], ambassador of the 
Russian Federation. The ambassador conveyed to the brother 
chairman a message from the Russian leadership on the current 
developments in our country, bilateral friendly relations, as 
well as issues of common concern. 
  During the meeting, the Russian ambassador reiterated the 
Russian Federation's constant position in support of Yemen's 
unity and stability. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

