<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Al-Bid Secession Call Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reaction to Al-Bid Secession Call Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Other Parties Condemn Secession </H4>

<F P=102> JN2205192694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2205192694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Executive Committee of the League of the Sons 
of Yemen Party has stated its commitment to all national 
constants -- national unity, democracy, and constitutional 
legality. 
  In a statement released today, the committee called the 
traitor al-Bid's declaration of secession a step without any 
basis in legality. In this move, al-Bid only speaks for himself 
and his renegade circle, which includes certain leaders of the 
Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP]. The traitor al-Bid's measures are 
illegal, and the actions taken by him and his coterie amount to 
national treason, the statement added. 
  'Abd-al-Rahman al-Jifri [member of the League of the Sons of 
the Yemen Party who has allied himself with al-Bid] has brought 
about his dismissal from the party, having turned his back on 
the party's principles, rules, and bylaws. The statement 
emphasized that whoever fails to safeguard his citizenship in 
our united Yemen forfeits his membership in the League of the 
Sons of Yemen Party. The statement called on the party leaders 
and rank and file in all the Republic of Yemen's governorates to 
abide by the letter and spirit of the party's bylaws and to 
implement its executive committee instructions. 
  Meanwhile, the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party, the Nasirite 
Popular Unionist Organization, the Yemeni Unionist Grouping 
Party, the Right Party, the Democratic Nasirite Party, the 
National Democratic Front, the Social Nationalist Party, the 
Leading Committee of the Fattah Corrective Stream inside the 
YSP, the Yemeni Socialist Party faction in the (?al-Maqwin) 
Governorate, the secretariat of the YSP in the Ibb Governorate, 
the Yemeni Human Rights Organization, the Yemeni Council for 
Peace and Solidarity, and the Disabled Society, have all 
denounced this criminal move on the part of the traitor al-Bid. 
They emphasized that this proclamation runs counter to the will 
of the people. They appealed to national public opinion and 
regional and world organizations to work to expose the plans 
seeking to discredit the homeland. They made plain that, far 
from mirroring the will of the YSP's rank and file, the decision 
only represents the secessionist gang led by al-Bid. 
  They emphasized that this secessionist step is illegal and 
that it violates the Republic of Yemen's Constitution on which 
the entire people of Yemen are agreed. They urged all popular 
forces to put up vigorous resistance to this band in the 
interest of safeguarding the homeland's unity, sovereignty, and 
territorial integrity. 
  The statement warned that any recognition of the 
secessionist 
regime by any country would amount to interference in the 
Republic of Yemen's domestic affairs and a blatant violation of 
international law. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

