<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Clashes, Military Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Clashes, Military Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    North To Observe 3-Day Cease-Fire </H4>

<F P=102> NC2005203294 Paris AFP in English 2029 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2005203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, May 20 (AFP)--The Yemen Government will 
observe a three-day cease-fire following 15 days of fighting 
with southern forces, the northern-controlled SABA' news agency 
reported Friday. 
  The ceasefire, effective from Saturday 0:00 a.m. (Friday 
2100 
GMT), was declared on the occasion of the Muslim 'Id al-Adha 
festival prior to Sunday's celebration of the fourth anniversary 
of the unification of South and North Yemen, the agency said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

