<DATE1>  20 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Clashes, Military Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Clashes, Military Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Further on Cease-Fire </H4>

<F P=102> LD2105033394 Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network in Arabic 
2300 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2105033394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Yemen, Sanaa radio announced this evening that 
the presidential council, the parliament, and the premiership 
council had decided on a three-day ceasefire. The same source 
added that all military activities will be suspended throughout 
the country beginning midnight on the occasion of the blessed 
Adha 'Id and the fourth anniversary of the unification of Yemen. 
  In Aden, very informed sources said that the Yemeni 
Socialist 
Party [YSP], after meetings that lasted 24 hours, decided to 
secede from Yemen and establish an independent state in the 
south. The same sources added that an official announcement and 
more details were expected any time now. 
  This announcement will be made as soon as the leader of the 
YSP, Ali Salim al-Bidh, returns to Aden from Hadramawt's eastern 
region. 

</TEXT>

