<H4>    Chief of Staff Notes Situation </H4>

<F P=102> NC2205113594 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1005 GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2205113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Brigadier General 'Abd-al-Malik 'Ali </F>
al-Sayyani, chief of the Armed Forces General Staff, by 
correspondent Mahmud al-Warraq; place and date not given-- 
recorded] 
  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] [Al-Warraq] Let us talk about 
the military situation at the front. 
  [Al-Sayyani] As you know, the fighting is proceeding well 
and 
is moving toward a resolution in favor of the constitutionally 
legitimate authorities. The forces have made noticeable 
progress on various lines along an approximately 1,000-km-long 
front, breaking the secession barrier forever; and they are now 
near Aden City and are tightening the blockade of the city. 
Forces in the east are at the gates of 'Ataq city, seeking to 
gain final control over Shabwah Governorate. Other forces also 
are advancing toward their targets steadily. 
  [Al-Warraq] What about the other side's claims? 
  [Al-Sayyani] The actual situation on the battlefield answers 
their claims and falsifications. 
  [Al-Warraq] If you were to address your forces, what would 
you say? 
  [Al-Sayyani] God willing, victory is close. We will defeat 
the forces of apostasy and secession that are trying to harm the 
brightest aspect of our Arab situation, Yemeni unity, and they 
will not be allowed to achieve their aims. 
  [Al-Warraq] How long will this take? 
  [Al-Sayyani] The time will be decided by the battle and the 
field situation. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

