<F P=102> NC2305073994 Paris AFP in English 0708 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2305073994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, May 23 (AFP)--A southern military spokesman 
denied Monday that northern Yemeni forces had captured a key 
base at 'Ataq, capital of the oil-producing province of Shabwah. 
  The claim by forces loyal to President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih 
was "totally unfounded, the spokesman told television in Aden, 
capital of the breakaway state headed by southern leader 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid. 
  A military spokesman in the capital Sanaa told the official 
SABA' news agency on Sunday that the 'Ataq base had fallen to 
government troops. 
  Northern forces also said they had been in control of 
another 
southern military base at al-'Anad since Friday and had now 
surrounded the southern stronghold of Aden. 
  'Ataq lies 130 kilometers (78 miles) east of Aden. 

</TEXT>

