<H3> <TI>   Salih Briefs Arab Leaders on Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Briefs Arab Leaders on Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2205074194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2205074194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lieutenant General brother 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, last night held telephone 
contacts with Saudi King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz, custodian of 
the two holy mosques; His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al 
Nuhayyan, president of the fraternal United Arab Emirates; 
struggler Yasir 'Arafat, president of the fraternal State of 
Palestine; Hafiz al- Asad, president of the fraternal Syrian 
Arab Republic; and Liamine Zeroual, president of the fraternal 
Democratic and Popular Republic of Algeria. 
  During these contacts, the leaders exchanged congratulations 
on the blessed 'Id al-Adha. Our country's relations with each 
of these leaders' country were also discussed. 
  The brother president briefed his brother leaders on the 
current developments in the Yemeni arena in light of traitor 
['Ali Salim] al-Bid's action against his Yemeni homeland and the 
Arab nation of announcing secession, which only represents 
himself and the small gang of the [Yemeni] Socialist party [YSP] 
that conspires against the Yemeni homeland, unity, people, and 
their democratic approach. 
  The president said that all the sons of our people in all 
the 
Yemeni governorates reject this crime and adhere to unity and 
democracy. They will continue to strongly defend and protect 
them from all plots and plotters, and to sacrifice all that is 
dear for their sake. He also said the masses of our Arab nation 
also reject this crime because they view the Yemeni unity as an 
important step on the road to achieving the pan-Arab objective 
of establishing comprehensive unity among the sons of the Arab 
nation. 
  The president expressed appreciation for the stands of the 
Arab brothers who have always been concerned about Yemeni unity 
and about supporting the Yemeni people's march under the banner 
of the Republic of Yemen, whose fourth anniversary is being 
celebrated by our people. 
  Another telephone contact was held last night between 
Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the 
Presidential Council, and his brother Colonel Mu'ammar 
al-Qadhdhafi, leader of the 1 September Revolution in Libya. 
  They exchanged congratulations on the blessed 'Id al-Adha 
and 
the current developments in our country in light of the crime of 
secession committed by traitor al-Bid. 
  The Libyan leader said he was very upset because of the 
current serious developments which threaten the march of the 
Yemeni unity. He also reiterated his support for the Yemeni 
unity and that of the Libyan people's support for the Yemeni 
people to safeguard the Yemeni unity, considering it a pan-Arab 
gain for the Arab nation and an advanced step on the road of 
achieving the comprehensive unity. 

</TEXT>

