<H3> <TI>   Visits, Inspects al-Mukalla Port </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visits, Inspects al-Mukalla Port </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2005191094 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1630 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2005191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The deputy chairman of the presidential council and 
secretary general of the Yemeni Socialist Party Central 
Committee, Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, late yesterday afternoon 
made an inspection tour of the wharves of al-Mukalla port, in 
the Khalf zone. 
  On arrival at the port, he was received by Brother Awad 
'Abdallah al-Murshidi, the deputy of the Governorate of 
Hadramawt, the director generals of the governorate, port 
officials, shipping corporation officials, and chamber of 
commerce members. 
  The brother secretary general was briefed during his visit 
on 
the activities at the port, shipping movements, and work going 
on to unload basic foodstuffs. He also heard a detailed 
briefing on programs to import commodities like wheat, rice, 
flour, milk products, and sugar, 33 tons of which arrived during 
the last two days. He was also briefed on the distribution of 
these commodities in the Governorates of Hadramawt, Shabwah, and 
al-Mahrah to ensure stable supplies and improve living standards. 
  He was accompanied on his visit by political bureau member 
Salim Muhammad Burran; Salih Abu-Bakr Bin Husaynun, minister of 
oil and mineral wealth; and a number of other officials. 

</TEXT>

