0630 GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2205123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Decision of the Provisional Council for National 
Salvation No. 2 [as heard]/1994 concerning the setting up of the 
State Presidential Council: 
  In the name of the people, after taking cognizance of 
Articles 1, 13 and 14, Paragraph B of the document on the 
proclamation of the Democratic Republic of Yemen, and the two 
decisions of the Provisional Council No. 1/1994 regarding the 
election of a chairman for the council, and No. 2 [as 
heard]/1994 for the proclamation of the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen, and the decisions of the Provisional Council for National 
Salvation at its meeting on 21 May 1994 concerning the election 
of the State Presidential Council, the Provisional Council for 
National Salvation has decided the following: 
  Article 1: The Presidential Council of the Democratic 
Republic of Yemen is formed as follows: 'Ali Salim al-Bid, Salim 
Salih Muhammad, 'Abd-al-Rahman 'Ali al-Ja'fari, 'Abd-al-Qawi 
Hasan Makkawi, and Sulayman Nasir Mas'ud. 
  Article 2: The Presidential Council assumes all its tasks 
and prerogatives in accordance with the provisions of the 
Constitution, and the document of the setting up of the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen. 
  Article 3: This decision takes effect from the date of its 
issuance. 
  Article 4: This decision will be published in the official 
gazette. 

</TEXT>

