<H3> <TI>   TNA Official, Others View Sudanese Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TNA Official, Others View Sudanese Peace Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2005195394 Khartoum SUNA in English 1615 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA2005195394 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nairobi, 20 May (SUNA) -- Deputy speaker of the 
Transitional National Assembly (TNA) Angelo Beda, Bahr al-Jabal 
State's Wali [Governor] Mrs. Agnes Lokudu and director of the 
peace department at the Foreign Ministry Mathiang Malwal have 
held here on Friday [20 May] a news conference on the 
resolutions of Juba political forum for peace forces. 
  Beda said that over 350 of the southern leaderships, besides 
representatives of international press and some ambassadors 
accredited to Khartoum, had participated in the forum, 
describing the forum as a "real gathering" to hear the voice of 
southern citizens, who confirmed their insistence on the unity 
of Sudanese soil and called for ending the war. 
  He added that the existing government is the only one that 
sat to negotiate seriously with the rebels' movement to end the 
southern Sudan war by presenting the Federal Government system 
as a comprehensive solution. 
  Mrs. Agnes Lokudu said that the forum asserted that the 
southern leaderships are aware of the Sudanese people's 
interests and not toys in the hands of government, as termed by 
the rebels' government and some hostile (?mass) media. 

</TEXT>

