<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Speaks on Occasion of 'Id al-Adha </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Speaks on Occasion of 'Id al-Adha </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105182694 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2105182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] On the occasion of the onset of the blessed 'Id 
al-Adha, brother President Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] went to 
the Hammam Lanouf martyrs cemetery in Tunis where he said a 
prayer for the souls of the martyrs amid a huge gathering of 
Palestinians cadres. 
  Brother President Abu-'Ammar delivered a brief speech in 
which he said: In the name of God, the compassionate, the 
merciful. [passage omitted] Dear brother Abu-Iyad [Salah 
Khalaf], Abu al-Hawl, Abu-Muhammad, Abu-Jihad [Brigadier General 
Muhammad], 'Atif, Abu-'Ali Iyad, Hamad ['Abd-al-Karim], Ghassan 
Kanafani, Abu al-Walid, Majid Abu-Sharar, Abu-al-Mundhir; 
brothers and beloved martyrs. While you rest in you paradise, 
the members of the Palestinian police force have entered 
Palestinian soil, the first liberated Palestinian land where the 
Palestinian flag is flying, and where we are going to set up the 
first Palestinian authority. 
  We are very aware of the significance of what we have 
achieved. We have not achieved everything that we wanted, but 
this is a step on the path of achieving what we want; a step 
toward the establishment of a Palestinian state whose capital 
will be Jerusalem. Some people see this as a long-term goal, 
but we see it as a short term one; we know we are right. 
  Once again brother martyrs, I would like to say that the 
promise that is between us will remain the same. We realize 
that the road to Jerusalem is a difficult and long one, but we 
will fly the flag of Palestine, the flag of the Arab nation, on 
the walls, churches, and mosques of Jerusalem. [passage omitted] 
  While we bid farewell today to sisterly Tunisia that stood 
by 
us and hosted this Palestinian work, this revolution, and 
leadership, we would like to express to our brother Zine el 
Abidine, to his hospitable people, and wise government our 
heartfelt thanks. We say to them we are in this path, the path 
of the Arab nation. We, the Palestinian people, represent this 
front, the Arab front on the sacred land, the first of the two 
qiblahs and the third of the holy places. We are an integral 
part of our Arab nation, we are an extension of this Arab land 
and this nation. The Arab columns who today enter Gaza and 
Jericho will tomorrow enter Nablus, Hebron, Tulkaram, Bethlehem, 
Ramallah, and every Palestinian territory. We have a date 
there, brothers. 
  The international resolution sought to undermine this 
revolution and the PLO, however, this blessed intifadah managed 
to put our people on the political map of the region. This 
result firmly puts our people on the political and geographic 
map, and consequently on the Middle East map. This baby 
requires all of us to work for him and with him, so that this 
baby will be able to grow and mature. 
  Once again, let met reiterate to you that our promise will 
remain the same promise and the pledge the same pledge. Let us 
stand together as one until the liberation of Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

