<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on Property Confiscated in Sudan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry on Property Confiscated in Sudan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2005151994 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2005151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Foreign Ministry issued a statement noting 
that yesterday at noon, it received a report from the Egyptian 
embassy in Khartoum saying that Sudanese security forces had 
expropriated three houses owned by Egyptian military attaches. 
One was occupied by the assistant air force attache, and the 
other two by embassy staff. 
  According to the report, the Sudanese security forces seized 
the residence of the Egyptian chairman of the joint irrigation 
authority of the Nile River water, in addition to 30 other 
residences owned by the Egyptian Irrigation Authority that were 
occupied by large numbers of Egyptian irrigation mission 
personnel and their families. The Sudanese security forces 
prevented these employees and their families from entering their 
homes. 
  At the same time, the Foreign Ministry statement adds, the 
Sudanese security forces expropriated the building of the 
Egyptian sports club in Khartoum. 
  In view of these measures, the Foreign Ministry immediately 
summoned the Sudanese charge d'affairs in Cairo to strongly 
protest the unacceptable and unjustified conduct which primarily 
targets Egyptian individuals and families residing in Sudan. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

