Arabic 1515 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2105165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Beirut--A Lebanese military source announced that 
Israel has committed a new act of piracy against Lebanon. 
  The source said an Israeli commando force, using two 
helicopters, kidnapped Hajj Mustafa al-Dirani, a Lebanese 
national resistance official, from his house in Qasr Naba at 
0200 today after this force infiltrated from the area between 
Jabal Kasrawan and al-Biqa'. [passage omitted] 

