<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Clashes, Military Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Clashes, Military Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Salih To Comply With Mubarak Call </H4>

<F P=102> NC2005204194 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 2022 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2005204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have just received the following from the central 
news desk: 
  Yemen President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih has announced his 
compliance with President Husni Mubarak's appeal to end the 
fighting in Yemen. President Salih affirmed to President Mubarak 
that a decision to end the fighting will be made in the coming 
hours. This was said in a telephone call that President Mubarak 
received from Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih a few 
moments ago. During the telephone call, President Mubarak 
stressed the need to make a decision to end the fighting among 
all parties and along all fronts. He emphasized that the Yemeni 
dispute can be resolved through dialogue, understanding, and 
amity. President Mubarak stressed that the fighting will not 
decisively settle the current crisis and noted the need to 
safeguard Yemen's unity and the interests of the Yemeni people. 
  Meanwhile, President Mubarak has received a telephone call 
from 'Ali Salim al-Bid, in which he underlined his commitment 
and compliance with Yemen [as heard]. 

</TEXT>

