<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders, Others Comment on Capture of al-Dirani </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leaders, Others Comment on Capture of al-Dirani </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Radio Reports IDF Operation </H4>

<F P=102> TA2105043694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0405 GMT 21 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2105043694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Last night, an IDF [Israel Defense Forces] force 
operating deep in Lebanon's al-Biqa' region captured and brought 
to Israel Mustafa al-Dirani, the head of a radical terrorist 
organization which took navigator Ron Arad captive in 1986. 
Al-Dirani heads an organization called the Believer's 
Resistance. An IDF spokesman reported that all our forces 
returned safely to base. 
  A REUTERS reporter in al-Biqa' reported that an IDF force 
flew by helicopter to al-Dirani's village of (al-Qassanabah), 
which is located 10 kilometers from Zahlah. The commando force 
kidnapped al-Dirani from his home. 
  IDF representatives have informed the Arad family about the 
operation. 

</TEXT>

