<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders, Others Comment on Capture of al-Dirani </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leaders, Others Comment on Capture of al-Dirani </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Weizman Discusses Kidnapping </H4>

<F P=102> NC2305074594 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 0700 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2305074594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kafr Killa Voice of the South </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israeli President Ezer Weizman has stated that the 
kidnapping of Mustafa al-Dirani demonstrates that Israel is 
doing its best for the sake of one of its soldiers. Israel will 
even step up its efforts in defense of the border area where 
army, security, and civilian personnel are deployed, Weizman 
added. He said: We will never abandon them because Israel is 
concerned with the security of this area and the fate of its 
inhabitants. 
  At the end of a visit to the border area to convey 
congratulations on 'Id al-Adha, President Weizman met the press. 
Present were the South Lebanese Army's [SLA] General Lahd, some 
of the area's key figures, Deputy Chief of Staff Amnon Shahaq, 
the commander of the northern sector, and the commander of the 
Liaison Force. Weizman said that peace in the Middle East rests 
with Syria and there is a link connecting Damascus, Beirut, and 
Amman on this issue. Weizman stressed that conducting 
unilateral talks with Lebanon depends on the Syrian president. 
I hope President Hafiz al-Asad will understand that the time is 
ripe for him to change his views concerning peace, he added. 
  Before leaving the border area, Weizman held a 30-minute 
closed meeting with Gen. Lahd. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

