<H4>    Sharon, Tzomet Praise Operation </H4>

<F P=102> TA2105153394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1500 GMT 21 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2105153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Likud Knesset Member Ari'el Sharon congratulated 
the Army and defense minister [for the operation in which 
Mustafa al-Dirani was abducted]. He hoped it would be the start 
of energetic action by which Israel would amass a bank of 
prisoners that eventually would ease the release of Ron Arad and 
the missing IDF [Israel Defense Forces] men. 
  The Tzomet party congratulated the IDF. Tzomet Chairman 
Refa'el Eytan said it was the only method the Arabs understood, 
and such actions should be continued with determination and 
cunning. 
  The chairman of the Meretz faction in the Knesset, Ran 
Kohen, 
praised the Army for its precise and perfect execution of the 
abduction. Normally he disapproves of carrying off people, but 
this time it was justified in view of the callousness and 
wickedness of the jailers of Israeli prisoners. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1400 GMT on 21 May 
adds: 
"The Moledet faction praised the IDF for the perfect execution 
of the operation."] 

</TEXT>

