<H4>    Cabinet Praises al-Dirani Operation </H4>

<F P=102> TA2205094294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 22 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2205094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning the cabinet heard a thorough briefing 
on the abduction of Mustafa al-Dirani, and the ministers praised 
the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] and the chief of staff on the 
operation. Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz adds that the 
ministers heard briefings on the situation in Gaza and Jericho, 
mainly by the coordinator of government activities in the 
territories. It was reported that unless funds are received in 
these areas, chiefly for the Palestinian police, the situation 
there will deteriorate. 
  Prime Minister Rabin reiterated his criticism of 'Arafat's 
call for a jihad to free Jerusalem, and once again rejected 
'Arafat's explanation. Foreign Minister Peres was more moderate 
in his remarks on the issue. The cabinet is currently dealing 
with the housing problem. 
  [Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew at 0920 GMT on 22 May carries 
a 
similar report, live from the Prime Minister's Office by 
political correspondent Udi Segal, which adds: "Ministers 
Shetrit and Tzaban noted the genocide taking place in Rwanda. 
The cabinet decided to express its shock in view of the murders 
in Africa. Foreign Minister Peres said he would examine the 
possibility of providing humanitarian aid to Rwanda."] 

</TEXT>

