<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sarid: 'Arafat Remarks Created `Crisis of Confidence' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sarid: 'Arafat Remarks Created `Crisis of Confidence' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2305103194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 23 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2305103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Environment Minister Yosi Sarid has warned that if 
Yasir 'Arafat does not retract his remarks on honoring 
agreements, Israel will not abide by the accord. Sarid, who has 
been closely involved in the autonomy negotiations, says that 
'Arafat's statements in the Johannesburg mosque earlier this 
month on signing agreements has created a crisis of confidence. 
The PLO leader, Sarid said, must declare his statements there 
null and void and reaffirm his total commitment to the peace 
process, in particular his support for a determined and open 
fight against terror. The environment minister was interviewed 
by Qol Yisra'el reporter Shulamit Schmerling during a visit to 
Haifa. 

</TEXT>

