<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres Leaves for U.S., South American Tour </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres Leaves for U.S., South American Tour </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2305044894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 23 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2305044894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres has left for an 
extended visit to the United States and South America. During 
his stay in Washington, he will meet with U.S. Secretary of 
State Warren Christopher and Vice President Al Gore. He will 
also reportedly try to encourage the U.S. and other nations to 
quickly speed up the funding of the Palestinian police force in 
the Gaza Strip and Jericho. Peres will later travel to Mexico, 
Colombia, and Chile. He is due to return to Israel on June 1st. 

</TEXT>

