<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council of Ministers Approves Supplemental Budget Act </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council of Ministers Approves Supplemental Budget Act </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305211394 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305211394 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] We begin with a meeting of the Council of 
Ministers at the presidential offices today. Mr. Liamine 
Zeroual, the head of state, chaired the meeting. In accordance 
with the agenda, at the beginning of its proceedings the council 
listened to a report by Prime Minister Mokdad Sifi on all the 
activities of his government since it was appointed. 
  In light of the report presented by the minister delegate 
for 
the budget, the Council of Ministers then studied and approved 
the Supplementary Budget Act 1994. The Supplementary Budget Act 
aims to implement austerity measures in public expenditure in 
order to reduce the total deficit in the state's finances; to 
provide additional financial resources to restructure and clean 
up public enterprises; to restructure banks; to limit the 
effects of the structural reform program on deprived social 
groups; to establish new tax measures aimed at promoting 
investment in conformity with and in transition to a market 
economy, on one hand, and at achieving economic revival so that 
national development can take off again, on the other. [passage 
omitted] 
  In his contribution to the Council of Ministers' discussion, 
the head of state insisted on the need to formulate a program 
for social protection, as well as undertaking work aimed at 
achieving economic effectiveness, because, as he explained, we 
must succeed not only on the economic level but also on the 
social level. [passage omitted] 
  In reviewing Algeria's foreign activities in the economic 
field, the head of state gave directives on the setting up of a 
joint ministerial committee to be headed by the prime minister. 
This committee will follow up the implementation of the 
agreement signed with the IMF. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

