<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Officials React to Rabin's Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian Officials React to Rabin's Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2305173494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 23 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2305173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here are some Palestinian reactions to Rabin's 
demand that Yasir 'Arafat reaffirm in writing his commitment to 
the peace process. 
  Palestinian Council Member Furayh Abu-Middayn says that 
crises were expected to crop up in the course of the 
negotiations, but if Israel seeks to limit the autonomy to the 
Gaza boundaries, it should say so candidly, rather than continue 
to come up with new pretexts. 
  Sa'ib 'Urayqat said the real danger to the peace process 
does 
not lie in Yasir 'Arafat's remarks, but rather in Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin's actions. 
  Jamil al-Tarifi, head of the Supreme Civilian Coordination 
Committee, told Qol Yisra'el correspondent Mark Weiss that 
Israel has posed preconditions for the resumption of 
negotiations that the PLO repudiates. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-60270 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes100dd_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-100 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Tibi: PNC To Revoke Anti-Israel Clauses </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Tibi: PNC To Revoke Anti-Israel Clauses </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2305194494 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1930 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2305194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Ahmad al-Tibi, Yasir 'Arafat's adviser, said 
tonight that the next Palestine National Council [PNC] 
convention will revoke Palestinian Covenant clauses contravening 
the Oslo agreement, including those calling for Israel's 
annihilation. 
  He announced that the PNC will convene soon, and for the 
first time in six years, the convention will be held in the Gaza 
Strip. 
  Dr. al-Tibi stressed that his remarks were made with PLO 
chief Yasir 'Arafat's knowledge. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

