<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th: No PNC Meeting in Gaza Until Calm Restored </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th: No PNC Meeting in Gaza Until Calm Restored </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2405105494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 24 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2405105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nabil Sha'th does not see a possibility of convening 
the Palestine National Council [PNC] in Gaza in the near future. 
Sha'th told Sa'id Mu'addi, a correspondent for Qol Yisra'el in 
Arabic, that the PNC could only be convened in Gaza after calm 
and security are restored. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

