<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fatah Leader on Plans for Palestinian Autonomy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Leader on Plans for Palestinian Autonomy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2405100394 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 21 May 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PM2405100394 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Muhammad 'Ali al-Qulaybi: "Palestinian Ambassador </F>
to Jordan Tells AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT: Palestinian Authority Council 
To Be Completed After 'Id al-Adha; Differences Between 'Arafat 
and Qaddumi Regarding the Return"] 
  [Text] Tunis -- Al-Tayyib 'Abd-al-Rahim, Palestinian 
ambassador to Jordan and Fatah Central Committee member, has 
stated that formation of the Palestinian Authority Council for 
Gaza and Jericho will be completed after the blessed 'Id al-Adha 
and will hold its first meeting in Cairo and subsequent meetings 
inside the occupied territory. 
  In a statement to AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Tunis, 'Abd-al-Rahim 
said that Fatah's Revolutionary Council approved the autonomy 
agreement signed by Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat and 
Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin on Wednesday 4 May in Cairo. 
  He added that the Council unanimously decided to return to 
Gaza and Jericho and to form committees to pass instructions and 
duties to the cadres to enter the homeland as soon as possible 
in accordance with a preconceived plan. 
  'Abd-al-Rahim denied divisions and differences of opinion 
between members of the Revolutionary Council which, he said, is 
a framework within which views and ideas interact, issues are 
discussed, and decisions are made on the basis of agreement and 
reconciliation. 
  He pointed out that there were two trends in the Council: 
One 
led by Faruq Qaddumi (Abu-al-Lutf), head of the Political 
Department, who wants the return to be gradual at all levels 
from the command to the lowest organization level. The other 
trend, led by President Yasir 'Arafat, believes that the entry 
of Fatah and PLO cadres into Gaza and Jericho should be done in 
full strength and weight because the situation is ripe for that 
and because the process of building the autonomy authority in 
Gaza and Jericho requires the pooling of all efforts and 
resources to ensure success of that experiment and, therefore, 
pave the way for PLO success in future steps aimed at setting up 
an independent Palestinian state with holy Jerusalem as its 
capital. 
  Al-Tayyib 'Abd-al-Rahim, who is also a member of Fatah's 
Revolutionary Council, confirmed that all the Council's members 
have expressed support for the decision to return to Gaza and 
Jericho in accordance with a specific plan and instructions for 
all cadres, and that 10 special committees have started their 
task of placing the cadres in their appropriate place within the 
national authority. These committees represent all the 
political, economic, security, educational, and other sectors 
under national authority powers. 
  The Fatah Central Committee member said that all Palestinian 
qualified patriots would participate in the process of building 
the Palestinian entity, and that the process would not be 
confined to qualified people from the factions because "the 
Palestinian authority belongs to all the Palestinian people and 
not just one group." 
  'Abd-al-Rahim said that he might be assigned the duties of 
the presidency's general secretariat. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-60278 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes100dd_94011" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-100 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jericho Mayor Discusses Situation, 'Arafat's Return </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jericho Mayor Discusses Situation, 'Arafat's Return </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2205065594 Cairo Voice of the Arabs in Arabic 0510 GMT 22 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2205065594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Voice of the Arabs </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone interview with Jericho Mayor Jamil Sabri Khalaf </F>
in Jericho, by Ashraf 'Abd-al-'Aziz in Cairo, date not given; 
from the "Dialogue From Afar" program] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] ['Abd-al-'Aziz] Mr. Khalaf, Dr. 
Nabil Sha'th visited Gaza and Jericho in the first such visit by 
a Palestinian official to Gaza and Jericho, the Palestinian 
self-rule areas. Can you tell us what happened during the 
meetings he held and the nature of his visit? 
  [Khalaf] Dr. Nabil Sha'th is one of the leaders who have 
worked and made great efforts to establish peace in the region. 
It is also very natural for him to be with us on two occasions: 
The first occasion is the entry of the Palestinian police and 
the second occasion is the 'Id al-Adha. Of course, his being 
with us leaves a very good impression and gives a feeling of 
security. He is an official of the PLO, under the leadership of 
Chairman 'Arafat. This leaves a very good impression with the 
forces and citizens and provides them with a great sense of 
security that a top-ranking Palestinian official, Mr. Nabil 
Sha'th, is visiting the area. 
  ['Abd-al-'Aziz] Israel doubts the ability of the Palestinian 
police to perform their security duties in the Palestinian 
territories. What can we say about the capabilities of the 
Palestinian police or the policeman? 
  [Khalaf] There is no doubt that every good citizen who likes 
peace and loves his country will consider himself a policeman 
and keep the peace and security. Naturally, the citizens of the 
city joined the policemen, and everyone is enjoying the fact 
that they are abiding by the law and applying it in order to 
provide peace of mind for every citizen. 
  ['Abd-al-'Aziz] Mr. Khalaf, Palestinian president 'Arafat 
will enter the Palestinian territories at the beginning of next 
month. What kind of reception he will be given by the 
Palestinian people? 
  [Khalaf] There is no doubt that there are many preparations 
under way to receive the Palestinian president on the 
appropriate date, which he himself will determine. The city is 
patiently awaiting his arrival. His return to the city and 
entry to the region will be a historic day. The cities of Gaza 
and Jericho are the first experiments for the Palestinian people 
in establishing peace. Praise be to God that autonomy has 
started in Gaza and Jericho. We welcome the president to his 
land and city and among his people. 
  ['Abd-al-'Aziz] Mr. Khalaf, there are reports that the 
Palestine National Council [PNC] will meet in Jericho. What can 
you tell us about this meeting, and when will it will be held? 
  [Khalaf] The date will be fixed by the president and the 
brothers in the PNC. We hope it will be a historic date in 
Jericho. It will be a historic starting point for the 
Palestinian people and we welcome the PNC members here. 
  ['Abd-al-'Aziz] Mr. Jamil Sabri Khalaf, Jericho mayor, we 
thank you very much for this telephone interview and wish you a 
happy 'Id al-Adha. We also wish the Palestinian people health 
and prosperity. 
  [Khalaf] Many happy returns to you, the Islamic and Arab 
nations, wherever you may be. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

