<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Palestinian Police Arrest 2 Israeli Settlers in Jericho </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Palestinian Police Arrest 2 Israeli Settlers in Jericho </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2405085294 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0830 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2405085294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two Israeli citizens were arrested by Palestinian 
policemen in Jericho and their personal weapons were 
confiscated. The two Israelis were released a short while ago. 
The men are residents of the Na'ama settlement, who apparently 
went to Jericho to shop. 
  The incident was reported to our correspondent in the 
territories Golan Yokhpaz today by residents of the Jordan Rift 
Valley. One of the men who was arrested is Arye Shahar, the 
security officer at Na'ama. Shahar managed to use his 
walkie-talkie to report that he and his friend had been detained 
and taken to the Palestinian police station in Jericho. Na'ama 
residents expressed great fury at what they called a flagrant 
violation of the Cairo agreement. The circumstances leading to 
the arrest of the two Israelis remain unclear, as does the 
reason for their release. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

