<F P=103> TA2405093294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Palestinian policemen arrested two settlers from 
Na'ama in Jericho and confiscated their handguns. Sa'adi Naji, 
the commander of the Jericho Police, apologized for the incident 
and explained that his men had acted wrongly because they had 
not understood their orders. The two settlers and their weapons 
were transferred to the regional coordination office. This was 
reported by our correspondents Gil Litman and Moti Amir. 

</TEXT>

