<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Source' on King Fahd's Message on Yemeni Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source' on King Fahd's Message on Yemeni Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105075494 Riyadh SPA in Arabic 2359 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105075494 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jeddah, 20 May (SPA) -- In a statement to SPA, a 
responsible source announced this evening that King Fahd 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz Al Sa'ud, custodian of the two holy mosques, 
may God preserve him, had earlier sent a message to His 
Excellency President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the 
Presidential Council of the Republic of Yemen, in which he 
expressed his hopes for an end to the fighting during the days 
of the blessed 'Id al-Adha, out of respect for this Islamic 
occasion. This took place when the beloved king received His 
Excellency Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, Yemeni planning and 
development minister, last Wednesday, 18 May. 
  The source went on to say: Consultations between the two 
sides continued on bringing about an end to the fighting. 
  At 1900 this evening, the custodian of the two holy mosques 
received a telephone call from his brother His Excellency 
President Salih, during which a number of matters were 
discussed. Chief among these was the Yemeni issue. 
  The source added: When the Yemeni mass media announced a 
three-day cease-fire this evening, effective from midnight, King 
Fahd Bin- 'Abd-al-'Aziz talked by phone with His Excellency 
President Salih and expressed his appreciation for the pleasing 
response regarding the cease-fire. 

</TEXT>

