<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Receives Letter From Libya's al-Qadhdhafi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Receives Letter From Libya's al-Qadhdhafi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2305095394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0800 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2305095394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Presidential Council chairman, yesterday received a letter from 
his brother, Colonel Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi, leader of the 1 
September revolution in Libya. The letter deals with the 
current developments in our country and Libya's firm, constant 
position that strongly supports Yemeni unity and rejects 
secession under whatever name, since Yemeni unity is a pan-Arab 
gain and an advance step along the path to embody the pan-Arab 
objective of comprehensive Arab unity. 
  The letter expressed the fraternal Libyan people's support 
for their brothers in the Yemeni Republic and their backing 
under the umbrella of unity and democracy. It also dealt with 
issues of interest to both fraternal countries. The letter was 
delivered by brother Sayfawi Yusuf, the charge d'affaires of the 
Libyan Brotherhood Bureau in Sanaa who met with the president 
yesterday. 
  The brother president praised the principled pan-Arab stand 
of the brothers in Libya, led by brother Col. Mu'ammar 
al-Qadhdhafi, who has devoted all of his life to the cause of 
Arab unity and who played a key role in supporting all steps and 
efforts that led to the Yemeni unity and the establishment of 
the Yemeni Republic and supporting the march of unity since it 
was launched on 22 May 1990. 
  The brother president asserted that Yemeni unity is here to 
stay. It will be safeguarded by the Yemeni people and their 
Armed Forces. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

