<H3> <TI>   Hadi Reportedly Killed in Car Crash </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hadi Reportedly Killed in Car Crash </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2305132794 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 23 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2305132794 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Reports by Lutfi Shatarah in London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
bureaus in Aden and Sanaa, Salwa al-Ustuwani in Damascus, Sawsan 
Abu-Husayn in Cairo, and Khalil Matar in Washington: "Reports 
Claiming Yemeni Defense Minister Killed in Road Accident"] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] According to unconfirmed 
reports, Colonel 'Abd-Rabbuh Mansur Hadi, the Yemeni defense 
minister appointed by President Salih in the place of Brigadier 
General Haytham Qasim Tahir, has been killed in a road accident 
in Sanaa along with Muhammad 'Abdallah al-Batani, minister of 
social affairs and security, and a number of southern military 
commanders loyal to former President 'Ali Nasir Muhammad. There 
has been no confirmation of these reports. 
  The reports also said that the Yemeni president had 
appointed 
his brother Colonel 'Ali Muhsin al-Ahmar as defense minister. 
  Yesterday was the fourth anniversary of unity between the 
north and the south. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

