<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reaction to al-Bid Secession Attempt Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reaction to al-Bid Secession Attempt Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Liberation Front: Action `High Treason' </H4>

<F P=102> JN2405155094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1506 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2405155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The General Secretariat of the Liberation Front 
Party has cabled Presidential Council Chairman Lieutenant 
General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and members of the council, the 
speaker and members of the House of Representatives Speakership 
Council, and the Cabinet, to denounce the secession declared by 
the war criminal and traitor al-Bid and his clique. The message 
dubbed the move a grievous crime and high treason as well as 
being in clear violation of the popularly-endorsed constitution. 
The secession was also described as a brazen deviation from the 
aims and principles of the Yemeni revolution for which droves of 
martyrs have fallen. This criminal action, the cable read, is 
the latest in a series of acts of sabotage, intrigues, and 
treason typical of the secessionist circle in the Socialist 
Party. 

</TEXT>

