<H3> <TI>   Airlines, Ships Warned Against Using Southern Ports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Airlines, Ships Warned Against Using Southern Ports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2305155094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1531 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2305155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the Transportation Ministry 
has stated that the Transportation Ministry wishes to draw the 
attention of all airlines and maritime shipping companies to the 
fact that the airspace over and the waters around the airports 
and seaports in the following areas: Aden, Hadhramaut, and 
al-Mahrah, are military zones. Consequently, flying, sailing, 
landing at airports, or docking at seaports in these areas may 
expose their aircraft and vessels to danger. The Government of 
the Republic of Yemen will not be responsible in any way for any 
damage or losses any company may incur as a result of violating 
these regulations. 
  Issued by the Transportation Ministry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

