<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statement Ridiculed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statement Ridiculed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2405125094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio in 
Arabic 2045 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2405125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A military source at the command of the Armed Forces 
of the Democratic Republic of Yemen has ridiculed a statement 
issued by a so-called responsible source at the Transport 
Ministry and broadcast by Sanaa radio this evening. The source 
stressed that the al-Ahmar gang is now in a difficult military 
position because it is incapable of threatening any of the air 
or sea ports of the Democratic Republic of Yemen. He confirmed 
that the Armed Forces of the Democratic Republic of Yemen are in 
total control of all the harbors and airports in this Republic 
and that they can fully guarantee the security and safety of 
these harbors and airports and provide the necessary services 
for ships and aircraft which call there. 
  The military source commented on the statement by a 
responsible source at the Transport Ministry to the effect that 
the Sanaa government is not responsible for damage or losses 
that might occur to any foreign company. The military source 
said that the government led by the al-Ahmar gang is no more 
than a smuggling and terrorist gang. It cannot ensure the 
safety of any foreign company just as it is incapable of 
protecting the security of the country and its citizens. The 
source concluded by saying there are a number of companies and 
individuals who have been subjected to looting, plundering, 
assassination, and kidnapping before the eyes and ears of the 
security forces of that corrupt authority. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

