<H3> <TI>   Pilots From South Urged To Join `Legitimacy' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pilots From South Urged To Join `Legitimacy' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2305155794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1532 GMT 23 May 93 </F>

<F P=103> JN2305155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Appeal by the defense minister;" date not given--read by </F>
announcer] 
  [Text] Out of our concern for the lives of the misled and 
helpless pilots and those who are under pressure, and out of our 
concern for the safety of the remaining warplanes that are still 
being manipulated by the rebellious, apostate, and secessionist 
gang--being state-owned planes whose prices have been paid by 
the people--we call on all those pilots not to obey the orders 
issued to them by the rebellious, secessionist gang and to fly 
their planes to any airport under the control of the legitimate 
authority to ask for landing permission and to join their 
brothers in the Air Force. They should be confident that they 
will receive the same treatment that their brothers are 
receiving in terms of rights and duties. It is better for them 
to be at the side of the people, unity, and constitutional 
legitimacy so that they will not be filled with regret after it 
is useless to be so. 
  [Signed] Staff Brigadier General 'Abd-Rabbuh Mansur Hadi, 
the 
defense minister 

</TEXT>

