<H3> <TI>   Shabwah Situation Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shabwah Situation Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2305174594 London MBC Television in Arabic 1700 GMT 23 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2305174594 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Clashes in Yemen today took place mainly in the 
oil-rich governorate of Shabwah. Foreign correspondents who 
visited al-Mukalla area in Hadhramaut said the southern forces 
are reinforcing their positions in Shabwah and that military 
aircraft are flying over the governorate, parts of which the 
northern forces claimed earlier they had captured. Civilians in 
Hadhramaut have been called up to assist the forces in Shabwah. 
  Meanwhile, political sources in Sanna say President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih is working on achieving swift military gains to 
pressure, to the greatest possible degree, the south should a 
cease-fire be reached. 

