BFN 

  [Text] The president, Mr. Farooq Ahmad Khan Leghari, left 
Lahore this morning on a two-weeks visit to the United States. 
The president was accompanied by the Punjab chief minister, Mr. 
Manzoor Ahmad Watto, and other members of the entourage. He was 
seen off at the Lahore Airport by the Punjab governor, Chaudhary 
Mohammad Altaf Hussain. The senior Punjab minister, Maqdoom 
Altaf Ahmad, and provincial ministers were also present. The 
president will have stopovers in London and Paris on his way to 
the United States. During his stay in the United States, the 
president, Mr. Farooq Ahmad Khan Leghari, is likely to meet a 
number of U.S. officials, as well as businessmen, to project and 
explain Pakistan's economic and foreign policies. 

