<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Denounces Israeli `Piracy' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Denounces Israeli `Piracy' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Muslims Urged To Carry Arms </H4>

<F P=102> LD2305181994 Tehran IRNA in English 1734 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ba'labakk, May 23, IRNA -- Former secretary general 
of Lebanese Hizballah, Shaykh Subhi al-Tufayli, here Monday 
urged Lebanese Muslims to carry arms and defend themselves 
against the Zionist regime. 
  Interviewed by IRNA, al-Tufayli criticized the Lebanese 
Government for its silence vis-a-vis the crimes being committed 
by the Zionist regime, and held the government responsible for 
the abduction of Mustafa al-Dirani, leader of the Mu'manah 
resistance group. Al-Dirani was abducted from his home in 
al-Biqa' by the Zionist commandos last Saturday. 
  "From now on Lebanese people cannot trust the security 
provided by the Lebanese Government," he said. 
  Al-Tufayli warned that silence of the Lebanese officials 
would further encourage the Zionist regime to continue its 
crimes and violate the human rights in Lebanon. 

</TEXT>

