<H3> <TI>   Paper Views New Israeli, Syrian Positions on Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Views New Israeli, Syrian Positions on Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2105090194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0720 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2105090194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 May (MENA)--AL-AHRAM newspaper reports 
that U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher's tour of the 
region this week was highlighted by the considerable change in 
Syrian and Israeli stands regarding a peaceful settlement. It 
notes the clear discussions regarding Israeli withdrawal from 
the Golan Heights and the possibilities of normalizing 
Syrian-Israeli relations in the future. 
  AL-AHRAM's editorial for tomorrow, Saturday 21 May, says 
that 
the current talk on the many differences between the stands of 
the two sides is only natural with such complex and intricate 
negotiations. It notes that on the other hand, this means 
negotiations now address many of the detailed issues and are not 
merely confined to generalities and principles that govern the 
negotiations process. 
  AL-AHRAM affirms that Egyptian-U.S. efforts will continue to 
provide hope for moving the Syrian-Israeli course along and 
clearly pushing it forward despite all appearances to the 
contrary. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

