<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabbani Refuses To Resign, Calls For Council </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabbani Refuses To Resign, Calls For Council </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105103794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2105103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Afghan President Borhanoddin Rabbani has accused 
Golboddin Hekmatyar, the prime minister of that country, of 
triggering the current round of fighting and the war during the 
past two years. He reiterated that he would not accept the 
opposition's request to give up power. 
  According to a Central News Unit report from Kabul, Rabbani, 
who was speaking during 'Id al-Adha prayers among his supporters 
in Jabal Saraj, north of Kabul, claimed: The government's 
resignation today would lead to chaos in the country. At the 
same time, the Afghan president said that if a grand council 
[shuray-e bozorg] were to be formed by the representatives of 
the people of Afghanistan, he would unconditionally accept the 
decisions of that council on selecting a president and a 
cabinet. He called for the cooperation of all factions for the 
formation of such a council in 40 days' time, when his term of 
office comes to an end. 
  The rival factions in the Afghan war are observing a 
cease-fire on the occasion of 'Id al-Adha. Kabul and the rest 
of Afghanistan's towns and cities have been calm so far. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-60361 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes100_p_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-100 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hekmatyar Rejects Proposal To Create Council </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hekmatyar Rejects Proposal To Create Council </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2205171994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2205171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Afghan Prime Minister Golboddin Hekmatyar [as heard] 
rejected yesterday's proposal by Borhanoddin Rabbani, the 
president of that country, about the formation of a grand 
decision-making council in Afghanistan within the next 40 days. 
  Hekmatyar, who was speaking at an interview with the Central 
News Unit in Kabul, said the motive behind forming that council 
was to extend the term of the presidency of Borhanoddin Rabbani 
and prolong the war and killings in Afghanistan. 
  He also declared his agreement with the formation of a 
coalition government and powersharing between the country's 
political parties and groups. 
  The Afghan prime minister also called for the holding of 
general elections in that country by a neutral government 
acceptable to all political parties and groups, but did not 
refer to the manner of forming that neutral government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

