<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin To Demand 'Arafat's Written Commitment to Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin To Demand 'Arafat's Written Commitment to Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Peres Echoes Call </H4>

<F P=102> TA2305192994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 23 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2305192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres says Yasir 'Arafat 
must reaffirm his commitment to all the components and 
appendixes of the Israeli-PLO Declaration of Principles. In 
addition, 'Arafat must reiterate his opposition to the use of 
force or violence in the relations with Israel. Thirdly, 
'Arafat must reiterate his pledge to resolve conflicts 
peaceably. Shim'on Peres says 'Arafat made a declaration in 
this spirit during their meeting in Oslo some 10 days ago, in 
the wake of the public disclosure of the first passage of the 
Johannesburg tape. 
  Shim'on Peres says 'Arafat must make all these 
pronouncements 
for all the world to hear, and not only in a talk between 
politicians. 
  Mr. Peres made these remarks after his meeting with the UN 
secretary general in New York. 

</TEXT>

